A hidden gem, that's for sure. This place is in the middle of nowhere, but the seafood is also out of this world, so it totally makes sense. The name, "and good food" is not a lie, we had clam cakes, fish and chips, fried shrimp, and a few other things. Boy was it all brilliant. The ice cream is also made with really good ingredients. They had a ice cream with cashews in it, and it really did have lots of nuts in it. I don't know how the owners can afford such high price quality ingredients and stay in business.  The owner is really nice too, and will come out and talk to you if the place is slow. I've heard weekends are very busy, but if you go there during the day, it's usually pretty slow. Would definitely recommend this to someone who likes seafood!
